                            <AnchorPane minHeight="0.0" minWidth="0.0" prefWidth="600.0">
                                 <children>
                                    <TextArea editable="false" prefHeight="370.0" prefWidth="600.0" text="In this game, the objective is to capture as many opponent pieces as possible, whilst keeping your captured pieces to a minimum. &#10;&#10;In order to move a piece, simply drag-and-drop it to the destination tile. The pieces you're allowed to move will be automatically highlighted with a dashed stroke around the piece. &#10;&#10;You can only move your piece in the forward-facing diagonal directions, unless it is a King. &#10;&#10;If a piece is denoted as being required to move, it must follow the rules in capturing; if an opponent piece can be captured, you will be required to capture it. If multiple capturing moves are available, you are given the choice of piece to move. &#10;&#10;Once a piece is moved, the turn ends. If you capture a piece with that move, you are given an additional move, and are required to take it. If the additional move cannot be taken, your move will be automatically cancelled. You are able to perform multi-leg capturing moves using this system. &#10;&#10;If your piece lands on the King's Row (the row closest to the opponent's side), your piece will be 'crowned'. This is indicated with an inner ring on the piece. When your piece is a King, it can move in any of the 4 diagonal directions. If the piece landing on the back row is not a King prior to this move, their player's turn will be forced to end, even if they have a move remaining. &#10;&#10;If you successfully capture an opponent's King, the capturing piece will be crowned, making it a King. This is termed 'regicide'. &#10;&#10;The game ends when one side loses all of their pieces to capturing. The individual with any pieces remaining/least captured pieces is the winner. &#10;&#10;The 'Player Scores' tab shows the score of each player. The 'Gameplay Rules' tab shows the rules of the game. The 'Gameplay Log' shows any error messages from the game, including attempts at illegal moves. If you are unsure why a move was rejected, see this window for more information. " wrapText="true" />
